ary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"BOUFFLERS","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English: nickname from Old French  <i>beau flour</i> ‘fair flower’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Gaucher","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Armand, Francoise, Jacques, Laurette, Lucien, Philippe.","French:","from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Walhari</i>, composed of the elements <i>walh</i> ‘stranger’ and <i>hari</i> ‘army’."],"variants":[{"name":"Coetzee","meanings":["Afrikaans: probably an altered form of Dutch <b>Goetzee</b>, which is of French Huguenot origin, probably from   Gaucher  . Alternatively, <i>Coetzee</i> may be an altered form of Dutch <b>Kuzee</b>, a habitational name recorded in the 16th century as <i>Cudsee</i> and <i>Cutsee</i>, from a toponym located in Zeeland, which may be interpreted as <i>Cut's-see</i> ‘watercourse of Cudo’.","History: Dirk Coetzee, born in Kampen in the Netherlands around 1655, died in Cape Town in 1725."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gaucher DE BOUFFLERS was born in 1197, in Boufflers, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, his father, Bernard DE BOUFFLERS, was 29 and his mother, Blanche DE NOUVION EN PONTHIEU, was 16. He